The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Dont try and manufacture shots
                                                                                                                   Dont try and manufacture shots
Work on your sideways movement to improve collection down the leg side            CRICKET ONLINE    Ravi Shastri                        
	I am a right-arm pacer. I am not too tall and would like to know whether I should continue bowling medium pace.              
	(Shivam Kr Roy, 14, Calcutta-12)              
	Of course you should carry on. Get stronger and fitter and you can bowl quicker.               
	I am a medium-pacer and play first division cricket in Calcutta. How does one bowl reverse swing?              
	(Abhishek Chowdhury, 23, Calcutta-14)              
	Its about working on the ball and having a good wrist action.               
	I am a right-arm medium-pacer. What are the essentials of inswing and outswing?               
	(Deborshi Mukherjee, 16, Calcutta-40)              
	You need a good action and good wrist action to be able to swing the ball both ways.               
	I am a right-arm medium pacer and often change my action to suit my needs. Can it pose problems to my bowling?              
	(Siddharth Sharma, 16, Howrah)              
	Too many changes will definitely effect your bowling.               
	While attempting the cut, I try to keep the ball down but often end up giving a catch to gully. Please help.              
	(Samiran Dey, 19, Calcutta)              
	Get on top of the ball and roll your wrists.               
	 I always get out after scoring a quick 20 or 30. Please suggest a remedy.              
	(Amit Dhar, 22, Calcutta-15)              
	Keep things simple. Focus on your concentration and on your strengths. Dont try and manufacture shots.               
	I am a righthanded batsman. Very often a sudden lapse in concentration leads to my dismissal after getting past 50. How can I correct this?              
	(Ratan Jana, 19, Siliguri)              
	Follow the methods Ive suggested above.               
	I am a righthanded batsman. On a turning pitch is it necessary to tackle a spinner by reaching to the pitch of every ball?              
	(R.S. Dutta, Calcutta)              
	Getting close to the pitch of the ball will be of huge help.               
	I am lefthanded batsman. I often fall leg before to inswinging deliveries. Please help.              
	(Sanjeev Behera, Guwahati)              
	Dont commit yourself early. And dont fall over.               
	I am a wicketkeeper and weak on the leg side. I always try and follow the ball coming out of the bowlers hand but the collection problem on the leg side persists. How can I improve?              
	(Subir Mohan Dey, 21, Calcutta)              
	Work on your footwork. Working on your sideways movements will help.                                                                                                                                                                           
